  "prompt": "How can I reset password of Instagram account without email?",
  "response": "If you've forgotten your Instagram password and don't have access to the email associated with your account, you can still reset your password using other methods. Here are the steps:\n\n### 1. **Reset Password Through Your Phone Number (if linked):**\n   - Open the Instagram app or go to the Instagram website.\n   - Tap **\u201cForgot Password?\u201d** on the login screen.\n   - Select **\u201cSend an SMS\u201d** or **\u201cCall\u201d** to receive a verification code on your linked phone number.\n   - Enter the code you receive and reset your password.\n\n### 2. **Reset Password Through Facebook (if linked):**\n   - Tap **\u201cForgot Password?\u201d** on the login screen.\n   - Select **\u201cLog in with Facebook.\u201d**\n   - If your Instagram account is linked to Facebook, you can reset your password through Facebook's recovery process.\n\n### 3. **Verify Your Identity:**\n   - If you don\u2019t have access to the email, phone number, or Facebook account linked to your Instagram account, you can try to verify your identity.\n   - Open the Instagram app, tap **\u201cForgot Password?\u201d** and then select **\u201cNeed more help?\u201d**\n   - Follow the instructions to verify your identity. Instagram may ask for:\n     - Your full name and username.\n     - A photo of yourself holding a code they provide.\n     - Additional information to confirm you\u2019re the account owner.\n\n### 4. **Contact Instagram Support:**\n   - If none of the above methods work, you can report the issue to Instagram directly.\n   - Go to the Instagram Help Center ([https://help.instagram.com/](https://help.instagram.com/)) and follow the steps to recover your account.\n   - Be prepared to provide proof of ownership (e.g., a photo ID, username, and previous details about the account).\n\n### 5. **Tips for Faster Recovery:**\n   - Use the same device and IP address you typically use to access Instagram.\n   - Provide as much information as possible to prove you\u2019re the account owner.\n\nIf you\u2019re unable to recover your account, you may need to create a new one. Make sure to link it to an accessible email or phone number for future recovery.",
